TZANEEN, February 25 – Two men were killed and one man was critically injured when a truck and two cars collided on the R71 in Magoebaskloof near Tzaneen in Limpopo on Saturday night, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics arrived at the scene and found that two men showed no signs of life, ER24 spokeswoman Annine Siddall said. “There was, unfortunately, nothing paramedics could do to save them and they were declared dead at the scene. Another man was in a critical condition and he was transported to Van Velden Hospital for further medical care.” A man who sustained moderate injuries in the collision was treated and transported to a nearby hospital by other emergency services on the scene. The cause of the crash was not yet known, Siddall said. – African News Agency (ANA)